 deixis and also sheds light on more elusive, epiphenomenal qualities such as a text’s ambience, atmosphere, power, ideology or persuasiveness. It also takes new strides in cognitive text analysis by exploiting experimental and ethnographic methods to empirically investigate readers’ reception of, and resistance to, texts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCognitive grammar. 0aDiscourse analysis. 4aLanguage & Linguistics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aBrowse, Sam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFilardo-Llamas, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGavins, Joanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarrison, Chloe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHart, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolland, Jeremy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoller, Veronika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRyan, Josie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSemino, Elena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStockwell, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWhiteley, Sara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311078042040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147445000340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474450003423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474450003/original  a978-3-11-078042-0  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  